-- Biggest rise in June since 2006 for Spanish mortgages approvals
-- 
-- Wed Aug 27, 2014 05:07AM EDT
-- None



MADRID, Aug 27 (Reuters) - The number of Spanish mortgages granted in June rose 19 percent year-on-year, National Statistics Institute INE said on Wednesday, the biggest monthly rise since March 2006.

In another sign of a gathering economic recovery, the number of mortgage approvals rose to 17,137 in June, while the average amount loaned was 98,682 euros, up 1.3 percent year-on-year.